.\" Manpage for _printf
.TH _PRINTF 3 "25 Nov 2025" "Version 1.0" "Custom C library"
.SH NAME
_printf \- prints formatted output to standard output

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "#include \"main.h\""
.br
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function partially replicates the behavior of the standard
.B printf
function.
It prints a string of characters to standard output, supporting a limited set of format specifiers.

The supported format specifiers are:

.TP
.B "%c"
Prints a single character.
.TP
.B "%s"
Prints a string of characters.
.TP
.B "%d"
Prints a signed decimal integer.
.TP
.B "%i"
Prints a signed decimal integer.
.TP
.B "%%"
Prints the percent character '%'.

All other characters in the
.B format
string are printed as-is.

.SH PARAMETERS
.IP format
A string containing text to print and format specifiers.
.IP ...
Arguments corresponding to the format specifiers in the format string.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the total number of characters printed to standard output.

.SH ERRORS
If an unsupported format specifier is encountered, the function prints '%' followed by the unknown character.
If
.B format
is
.RI NULL ,
the behavior is undefined.

.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
_printf("Char: %c, Name: %s, Number: %d, %%\n", 'A', "Alice", 42);
.nf
This prints:
.Carriage Return
Char: A, Name: Alice, Number: 42, %
.fi

.SH NOTES
- Internal helper functions used include
.B print_char,
.B print_string,
.B print_int,
and
.B print_percent.
- Characters are printed one by one using
.B _putchar.
- Only the listed format specifiers are supported.
